      <div id="about" class="span8">
        <h3><a href="#top" class="nav">About &nbsp; <i class="icon-arrow-up"></i></a></h3>
        <p>Imagine a world where your web applications are independent and not on rental. Backend services are generalized and you have the option of choosing where your app can tie-in to make use of server resources. Your user data, and app functionality live on, beyond any one vendor's control.</p>

        <p>By implementing a polyglot server that can speak all of the various protocols and APIs of the web today, Sockethub aims to solve one piece of that puzzle. Exposing a single abstracted interface to application developers, this open platform can be run on any server, and provides social and other interactive messaging functionality to the application. Adding one more building block to the goal of server-independent, server-side functionality, Sockethub can help to free our web applications from vendor lock-in.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="span2">
        <p></p>
      </div>
    </div>


